Package: CesaR
Type: Package
Title: CNV Estimation with CBS Panel Segmentation and Anchor Recalibration
Version: 0.1.0
Date: 2026-06-26
Authors@R: c(
    person("Shuai", "Ni", email = "nishuai@yahoo.com", role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(affiliation = "Huazhong University of Science and Technology")),
    person("Huazhong University of Science and Technology", role = "cph")
    )
Description: Detects copy number variations (CNVs) in targeted sequencing
    panels. Compared to the older Cesar package, CesaR adds the missing front
    of the pipeline: a panel-of-normals-driven master depth estimate and
    CBS-based re-segmentation of the raw panel BED, so the anchor-correlation
    training step operates on segments that truly reflect coverage structure
    rather than user-supplied bins. Same-gene anchor exclusion is on by
    default. Designed for low-amplitude CNV detection in EGFR, ERBB2, MET and
    similar targets from circulating tumor DNA or tissue panels.
